# PackRat MCP Server — local development environment variables
# Copy this file to .dev.vars (never commit .dev.vars)

# Post-refactor: this file contains only the JWKS-fetch target.
# The MCP worker is a pure protected resource — it validates JWTs against
# `${PACKRAT_API_URL}/api/auth/jwks` via `token-verify.ts`. No DCR / KV /
# login state lives here anymore.

# Required: base URL of the PackRat API (hosting the Better Auth OAuth
# authorization server and the JWKS endpoint).
# Local: http://localhost:8787
# Production: https://api.packrat.world
PACKRAT_API_URL=http://localhost:8787

# Optional: build identifier (U16). Surfaced by `/status` as `commitSha`
# so a reviewer can correlate a running Worker with a specific commit.
# Set at deploy time, NOT in source — operators / CI use:
#   wrangler deploy --var MCP_COMMIT_SHA:$(git rev-parse --short HEAD) --env prod
# (U17's mcp-deploy.yml does this automatically). When unset, `/status`
# returns the sentinel string 'unknown'. Public, not a secret.
# MCP_COMMIT_SHA=

# ── Bindings (NOT secrets — declared in wrangler.jsonc) ──────────────────────
# The following are wired up as Cloudflare bindings in wrangler.jsonc and
# automatically present in the Worker's `env` at runtime. They do NOT belong
# in .dev.vars. Listed here so an engineer onboarding the package can find
# the canonical location:
#
#   MCP_TOOLS_RL   — Workers Rate Limiting binding. Keyed per-call for tool
#                    dispatch (`${userId}:${toolName}`, where `userId` is the
#                    JWT `sub` claim). Configured under the `rate_limiting`
#                    block in wrangler.jsonc with a 60/60s budget; see
#                    docs/mcp/runbook.md § "U14 rate limiting" for the
#                    operator overview. In local `wrangler dev` and `vitest`
#                    runs the binding may be absent — the call site falls
#                    back to "allowed" so dev doesn't break.
